01:11:52,480 --> 01:11:54,060
Dad...

727
01:11:55,200 --> 01:12:00,820
OK. A little ethics. You're walkin' down
the street. You find a suitcase full of money.

728
01:12:00,910 --> 01:12:05,320
There's nobody around. No human person
is in evidence. What do you do?

729
01:12:05,410 --> 01:12:07,820
A: You keep the money.

730
01:12:07,920 --> 01:12:12,380
B: You use it to buy gifts
for your friends and your loved ones.

731
01:12:12,460 --> 01:12:15,420
C: You give it to the poor.

732
01:12:16,170 --> 01:12:19,340
D: You turn it in to the police.

733
01:12:19,430 --> 01:12:21,840
- Dad, this is really stupid.
- Kim!

734
01:12:21,930 --> 01:12:23,890
- I'd keep the money.
- Simmer down.

735
01:12:23,970 --> 01:12:25,220
Edward?

736
01:12:26,560 --> 01:12:30,640
Hey, how about after dinner we go down
to the bowling alley? That'd be fun.

737
01:12:30,730 --> 01:12:32,690
You're not seeing Jim tonight?

738
01:12:32,770 --> 01:12:34,270
No.

739
01:12:35,070 --> 01:12:37,140
We had the coolest show and tell today.

740
01:12:37,240 --> 01:12:42,110
This kid brought in a box of baby possums.
Ten, maybe twelve. Totally naked.

741
01:12:42,200 --> 01:12:46,360
- No hair at all.
- Honey, your father isn't finished yet.

742
01:12:46,830 --> 01:12:49,580
Thank you, dear. Edward, we're waiting.

743
01:12:52,670 --> 01:12:54,750
Give it to my loved ones?

744
01:12:57,970 --> 01:13:02,380
Oh, Edward, it does seem that
that's what you should do, but it's not.

745
01:13:05,350 --> 01:13:09,730
You dope, everybody knows
you're supposed to give it to the police.

746
01:13:11,350 --> 01:13:13,150
Good thinking, Kevin.

747
01:13:13,230 --> 01:13:15,310
Well, think about it, you guys.

748
01:13:15,900 --> 01:13:19,350
I mean, that's the nicer thing to do.
That's what <i>I would do.

749
01:13:19,450 --> 01:13:25,370
We're not trying to confuse him, we're trying
to make things easier, so cut the comedy.

750
01:13:25,450 --> 01:13:28,570
I am being serious, Dad.
It's a much nicer thing to do.

751
01:13:28,660 --> 01:13:31,240
Forget nice. We're talking right and wrong.

752
01:13:31,330 --> 01:13:32,710
Shut up!

753
01:13:32,790 --> 01:13:38,910
Oh, goodness! No wonder poor Edward can't
learn right from wrong, living in this family!

754
01:13:39,010 --> 01:13:42,010
Well, did you hear
what he did to Peg's curtains?

755
01:13:42,090 --> 01:13:46,010
It's unbelievable they're having
their party anyway. Are you going?

756
01:13:46,100 --> 01:13:47,810
I don't think so.

757
01:13:47,890 --> 01:13:51,220
He practically raped Joyce,
threatening her with those knives.

758
01:13:51,310 --> 01:13:53,100
It's a miracle she escaped.

759
01:13:53,190 --> 01:13:55,390
I have nothing against Bill and Peg, but...

760
01:13:55,480 --> 01:13:58,770
I know. They've got that
teenage daughter in the house.

761
01:13:58,860 --> 01:14:01,780
Those poor things!
After what happened to me...

762
01:14:01,860 --> 01:14:03,610
Can you imagine?

763
01:14:03,700 --> 01:14:06,070
What did you say about the Christmas party?

764
01:14:06,160 --> 01:14:08,200
I said I hoped we could make it.

765
01:14:08,290 --> 01:14:10,200
I lied too.

766
01:14:30,180 --> 01:14:33,100
Edward? Do you want to
give me that new haircut?

767
01:14:33,690 --> 01:14:35,980
- Again?
- Yeah, sure!

768
01:14:36,060 --> 01:14:40,440
It makes me proud to have you
as my own personal hairdresser.

769
01:14:43,030 --> 01:14:44,860
- Hi, honey.
- Hi.

770
01:14:44,950 --> 01:14:47,980
- Kevin, want to play scissors, paper, stone?
- No.

771
01:14:48,080 --> 01:14:51,330
- Why?
- It's boring. I'm tired of always winning.

772
01:14:51,410 --> 01:14:54,580
- People's feelings, please. A few manners!
- I'll be outside.

773
01:14:54,670 --> 01:14:59,000
Never you mind, dear.
Just... cut away. Cut away.

774
01:15:04,300 --> 01:15:06,380
<i>* I saw three ships come sailing by

775
01:15:06,470 --> 01:15:09,170
<i>* On Christmas day, on Christmas day

776
01:15:09,260 --> 01:15:11,970
<i>* I saw three ships come sailing by

777
01:15:12,060 --> 01:15:14,130
<i>* On Christmas day in the morning

778
01:15:21,900 --> 01:15:25,570
It needs something... else.
What do you think, honey?

779
01:15:25,660 --> 01:15:28,570
- More bells?
- More bells. OK.

780
01:15:28,660 --> 01:15:31,690
Mom, do you really think
we should be having this party?

781
01:15:31,790 --> 01:15:34,570
Of course I think
we should be having this party.

782
01:15:34,660 --> 01:15:41,330
It's just what we need to calm things down,
and... everything'll go back to normal. Hm?

783
01:15:43,170 --> 01:15:45,330
Do you have any more bells, honey?

784
01:17:31,450 --> 01:17:32,310
Hey!

785
01:17:37,330 --> 01:17:39,540
Now you've done it.

786
01:17:39,620 --> 01:17:42,110
It's just a scratch, Jim, really. It's OK.

787
01:17:42,210 --> 01:17:45,250
- Touch her again and I'll kill ya.
- It's no big deal.

788
01:17:45,340 --> 01:17:48,010
- Call a doctor. He skewered Kim.
- No!

789
01:17:48,090 --> 01:17:49,920
Stay away from her. I mean it!

790
01:17:50,010 --> 01:17:54,300
You can't touch anything without ruining it.
Why do you hang around here anyway?

791
01:17:54,390 --> 01:17:58,880
I want you to sit right down
and wait for me to bring you some ice.

792
01:17:58,980 --> 01:18:01,510
Stay right there. I'll be right back.

793
01:18:01,600 --> 01:18:06,730
<i>* On Christmas day in the morning

794
01:18:07,570 --> 01:18:09,980
Get the hell outta here!

795
01:18:10,530 --> 01:18:13,070
Get the hell out! Go! Freak!

796
01:18:13,820 --> 01:18:15,980
Hey, Edward, where are you goin'?

797
01:18:23,830 --> 01:18:25,490
Where is he?

798
01:18:25,590 --> 01:18:28,290
- He tried to hurt you.
- He did not, and you know it.

799
01:18:28,380 --> 01:18:30,840
Are you nuts? I just saw him!

800
01:18:30,920 --> 01:18:35,800
Jim, I don't love you any more.
I just want you to go, OK? Just go!

801
01:18:36,600 --> 01:18:38,300
Are you serious?

802
01:18:38,390 --> 01:18:40,960
And lose you to that? He isn't even human.

803
01:18:41,060 --> 01:18:43,760
Just get out of here, OK? Just go!

804
01:18:51,780 --> 01:18:53,820
Dad, did you see where Edward went?

805
01:18:53,910 --> 01:18:56,440
I don't know. He just waltzed down the street.

806
01:18:56,530 --> 01:18:59,490
- We have to find him, Mom.
- Your father will find him.

807
01:18:59,580 --> 01:19:01,780
Go on in the house. I'll take care of it.

808
01:19:01,870 --> 01:19:05,210
I'll go find him.

809
01:19:21,270 --> 01:19:22,550
Edward!

810
01:19:22,640 --> 01:19:24,720
I'm calling the police!

811
01:20:12,610 --> 01:20:15,890
See all that blood, sweetie?
And it's just a little cut.

812
01:20:17,860 --> 01:20:19,320
Oh!

813
01:20:26,210 --> 01:20:28,700
Hello. I'm here to see the man with the hands.

814
01:20:30,340 --> 01:20:31,960
Ohh!

815
01:20:32,840 --> 01:20:35,000
- Uh...
- He's not here. Thank you.

816
01:20:36,010 --> 01:20:38,210
Oh, dear.

817
01:20:39,970 --> 01:20:42,300
Helen, did you actually see him?

818
01:20:42,390 --> 01:20:43,970
Yes! Look!

819
01:20:49,690 --> 01:20:51,810
I'm looking for the man with the scissors.

820
01:20:51,900 --> 01:20:55,310
- Thank God you're here.
- He went right down that way, sir.

821
01:20:55,400 --> 01:20:58,980
All right, calm down, calm down.
Go on home. We'll handle it.

822
01:20:59,070 --> 01:21:00,900
Just go home.

823
01:21:00,990 --> 01:21:04,910
- A... a demon. A demon.
- You gotta do somethin'!

824
01:21:12,540 --> 01:21:15,040
I'm sure your father'll find him soon.

825
01:21:15,760 --> 01:21:17,830
What time is it?

826
01:21:18,380 --> 01:21:22,330
It's almost 8.30. Great party, huh?

827
01:21:22,430 --> 01:21:24,510
Mom, where are they?

828
01:21:26,060 --> 01:21:29,060
- God, I hope he's OK.
- So do I, honey.

829
01:21:34,520 --> 01:21:38,310
You know, when I brought Edward
down here to live with us...

830
01:21:39,740 --> 01:21:42,360
...I really didn't think things through.

831
01:21:43,410 --> 01:21:46,580
And I didn't think about
what could happen to him.

832
01:21:47,910 --> 01:21:51,410
Or to us. Or to the neighbourhood.

833
01:21:53,790 --> 01:21:55,870
And now I think that maybe...

834
01:21:57,630 --> 01:21:59,710
...it might be best if he goes...

835
01:22:01,220 --> 01:22:03,290
...back up there.

836
01:22:04,050 --> 01:22:06,210
Because at least there he's safe.

837
01:22:08,600 --> 01:22:11,270
And we'd just... go back to normal.

838
01:22:13,860 --> 01:22:17,350
I got halfway to the Whitmans'.
I didn't see him anywhere.

839
01:22:17,440 --> 01:22:19,680
Let's get in the car and go look for him.

840
01:22:19,780 --> 01:22:21,770
- Where's Kevin now?
- At Max's.

841
01:22:21,860 --> 01:22:23,690
Oh, for God's sakes!

842
01:22:23,780 --> 01:22:26,450
- Where do you think you're goin'?
- With you guys.

843
01:22:26,530 --> 01:22:30,950
- You stay here in case somebody shows up.
- We'll be right back, dear.

844
01:23:09,830 --> 01:23:11,900
Police!

845
01:23:48,700 --> 01:23:50,780
Edward?

846
01:23:53,620 --> 01:23:55,280
Are you OK?

847
01:23:56,670 --> 01:23:58,460
Yes. Are <i>you</i> OK?

848
01:24:02,670 --> 01:24:04,460
Where is everybody?

849
01:24:05,180 --> 01:24:07,250
Out looking for you.

850
01:24:13,310 --> 01:24:15,220
Hold me.

851
01:24:29,030 --> 01:24:30,440
I can't.

852
01:24:59,190 --> 01:25:03,600
I know it's a little early
for Christmas, Edward, but...

853
01:25:06,990 --> 01:25:09,060
...I have a present for you.

854
01:27:06,860 --> 01:27:09,310
Forget holding her hand.

855
01:27:09,400 --> 01:27:11,970
Picture the damage he could do other places.

856
01:27:12,070 --> 01:27:14,150
Yeah. That's sick.

857
01:27:19,330 --> 01:27:22,740
Ugh! I feel like I'm gonna pass out
or puke or something.

858
01:27:22,830 --> 01:27:25,320
Later. First, take me to her house.

859
01:27:25,420 --> 01:27:27,290
Come on. Don't make me drive.

860
01:27:27,380 --> 01:27:28,920
Just do it!

861
01:27:29,460 --> 01:27:31,460
Jesus. Maybe she <i>was</i> right about you.

862
01:27:31,550 --> 01:27:33,620
- Just drive!
- Relax!

863
01:27:37,970 --> 01:27:40,930
- See you tomorrow. Call me.
- All right.

864
01:27:59,160 --> 01:28:01,450
Have they caught him yet?

865
01:28:02,200 --> 01:28:05,450
- Who?
- Him! That... that cripple.

866
01:28:09,090 --> 01:28:11,040
Let me know when they do.

867
01:28:13,130 --> 01:28:15,210
Let us all know, OK?

868
01:28:16,260 --> 01:28:18,340
Like a good boy.

869
01:28:38,910 --> 01:28:40,370
Kevin.

870
01:28:44,660 --> 01:28:47,040
- Urgh!
- Are you OK?

871
01:28:47,120 --> 01:28:48,620
- It's OK.
- Ow!

872
01:28:49,710 --> 01:28:51,790
Ow! Ow!

873
01:28:52,460 --> 01:28:54,620
- Edward, stop!
- I'm your friend.

874
01:28:59,220 --> 01:29:00,710
Help us!

875
01:29:03,260 --> 01:29:06,100
What are you doing? Get away from him!

876
01:29:13,400 --> 01:29:14,650
Hey...

877
01:29:14,730 --> 01:29:16,610
- Let go of me!
- What?

878
01:29:16,690 --> 01:29:18,490
Kevin!

879
01:29:25,200 --> 01:29:28,290
- Get away!
- Edward, come home. Come home!

880
01:30:00,030 --> 01:30:01,060
Run.

881
01:30:28,640 --> 01:30:32,220
Kevin's all right!
It was just the tiniest scratch!

882
01:30:32,310 --> 01:30:36,610
He's gone. Let's not bother him, all right?
Let's just leave him alone.

883
01:30:45,120 --> 01:30:47,190
Go on, run.

884
01:30:51,750 --> 01:30:54,500
- What happened? Is he dead?
- Did you get him?

885
01:30:55,170 --> 01:30:58,290
It's all over. Go on home.
There's nothing more to see.

886
01:30:58,380 --> 01:31:03,010
What happened out there?
I want to know! I want some answers!

887
01:31:03,090 --> 01:31:05,170
It is all over.

888
01:31:05,260 --> 01:31:08,180
Where is he? Where is he?

889
01:31:09,600 --> 01:31:12,770
Get back here!
I wanna ask you something!

890
01:31:19,030 --> 01:31:21,270
Look at that! I don't believe this.

891
01:31:22,570 --> 01:31:24,560
They don't have him. I'm goin'.

892
01:31:24,660 --> 01:31:26,730
No! That's not a good idea.

893
01:32:32,180 --> 01:32:34,260
They're coming?

894
01:32:36,810 --> 01:32:38,800
Did I hurt Kevin?

895
01:32:38,900 --> 01:32:42,430
No, he's OK. Mostly he was just scared.

896
01:32:44,440 --> 01:32:47,110
Edward, I was so afraid.

897
01:32:47,740 --> 01:32:49,980
I thought you were dead.

898
01:32:57,710 --> 01:32:59,250
I didn't.

899
01:33:08,050 --> 01:33:09,550
No!

900
01:33:19,150 --> 01:33:20,810
No!

901
01:33:20,900 --> 01:33:22,890
Jim, stop!

902
01:33:22,980 --> 01:33:24,440
No!

903
01:33:39,830 --> 01:33:40,860
No!

904
01:33:44,460 --> 01:33:47,330
Stop it. Or I'll kill you myself.

905
01:33:54,510 --> 01:33:56,170
Aagh!

906
01:33:58,480 --> 01:34:01,230
Hey! I said stay away from her!

907
01:35:01,370 --> 01:35:03,200
Goodbye.

908
01:35:14,510 --> 01:35:16,340
I love you.

909
01:36:04,560 --> 01:36:06,430
I-Is he in there?

910
01:36:08,610 --> 01:36:10,350
He's dead.

911
01:36:14,240 --> 01:36:16,310
The roof caved in on him.

912
01:36:17,370 --> 01:36:19,440
They killed each other.

913
01:36:22,410 --> 01:36:24,990
You can see for yourselves.

914
01:36:27,330 --> 01:36:28,660
See?

915
01:36:37,800 --> 01:36:39,880
I'm goin' home.

916
01:36:48,730 --> 01:36:50,810
Joyce...

917
01:37:08,000 --> 01:37:10,080
She never saw him again.

918
01:37:11,880 --> 01:37:14,000
Not after that night.

919
01:37:14,840 --> 01:37:16,920
How do you know?

920
01:37:23,680 --> 01:37:25,760
Because I was there.

921
01:37:26,430 --> 01:37:30,180
You could have gone up there.
You still could go.

922
01:37:31,520 --> 01:37:33,900
No, sweetheart.

923
01:37:33,980 --> 01:37:36,060
I'm an old woman now.

924
01:37:37,030 --> 01:37:39,820
I would rather him remember me
the way I was.

925
01:38:14,270 --> 01:38:16,350
How do you know he's still alive?

926
01:38:19,110 --> 01:38:21,270
I... don't know.

927
01:38:21,360 --> 01:38:23,770
Not for sure, but...

928
01:38:24,370 --> 01:38:26,660
I believe he is.

929
01:38:36,000 --> 01:38:40,220
<i>You see, before he came down here...</i>

930
01:38:41,130 --> 01:38:43,210
<i>... it never snowed.</i>

931
01:38:47,520 --> 01:38:49,970
And afterwards...

932
01:38:50,060 --> 01:38:52,140
...it did.

933
01:38:53,350 --> 01:38:58,270
If he weren't up there now,
I don't think it would be snowing.

934
01:39:00,860 --> 01:39:04,310
Sometimes you can still catch me
dancing in it.

935
01:44:43,460 --> 01:44:51,080
Visiontext subtitles by Paul Sofer

936
01:44:52,840 --> 01:45:00,470
ENGLISH HOH